To Raging Fury.  SoT had admitted partial fault (read: PARTIAL!!!! fault).  What we are looking for out of you is an admission of at least some fault in the matter and some understanding of our position.  We feel that we are being punished twice (once by being forced to destroy Clerise's BP and twice by being forced to give you a Donal's BP) for an incident that was not entirely our fault, this (along with the whole betrayal thing I spoke about a few posts ago) infuriates us to no end.  We are looking for some sort of cooperation on your part, not this holier-than-thou attitude that you all present in pretending to be infalable.  A compromise between our two guilds and GM Vaylin wherein one of the punishments levied against us via your /reports and our lack of /reports /pissandmoaning to GMs is lifted would be preferable.  I do not pretend that either of our guilds should be beyond punishment so I would not presume to ask you to remove your petition (note: I still think you're lower than pond scum for petitioning in the first place, but that is history and cannot be changed...we must deal with the present).  Case in point, were a conference between Eberan, our rep, and Vaylin to result in either a) clerise keeping her BP and you getting a Donals or b) clerise destroying her earned BP and us keeping the Donal's earned in a calm, fair matter then I believe we would be inclined to call this issue ended, as we can in no way go back and change the past.  However, we will not be deterred from our chosen path based on twisted logic, out of context quotes, partial logs, and flaming (please keep Slitz on a leash people, he's making you all look bad).  <br>
<br>
I have gone out of my way not to allow my feelings to come to bare here and cause me to mindlessly flame you, I would expect no less from RF in this case where flames are not warranted by either side if we intend to get through this without causing WW3.<br>
