I didnt want to get involved in this, but seeing a &quot;war&quot;<br>
on the horizon really doesnt appeal to me either. <br>
<br>
So here is my personal (I dont represent RF, yada, yada)<br>
try at maybe getting us back or at least closer to the good<br>
old relationship betweem SoT and RF.<br>
<br>
I think we all need to take a deep breath here and look<br>
at the situation without the emotional baggage.<br>
<br>
RF and SoT had a good relationship based on respect and<br>
honesty. This kind of relationship between guilds doesnt<br>
just appear from nowhere but rather from a lot of grouping <br>
and help between members of both our families. Personally I<br>
have friends in SoT that I respect and I know to be honest <br>
people and this situation will not make me change my mind on <br>
that. I am sure a lot of SoT and RF members are in the same<br>
situation and wont start thinking their friends just became evil.<br>
<br>
RF members werent snatched by the an evil dragon during the night to be replaced by evil changelings either.<br>
<br>
Can SoT people think about this just a few minutes?<br>
Its all I ask.<br>
<br>
SoT feels betrayed because of the friendship involves between our two guilds before what happened in PoG because they think RF stole their mob on purpose.<br>
As was said before, that wasnt the case. It was never done on purpose like some people have been accusing RF of doing.<br>
<br>
Let me try to put myself in SoT mindset when the PoG event happened (I may be off the track completely, but I am willing to try):<br>
<br>
1) SoT goes to PoG and as per their tactics (each guild has some) clear the protectors<br>
2) When almost finished clearing the protectors, they see us RF pull Treah.<br>
3) Someone from SoT calls FFA on the mob in the heat of the moment due to assuming we were stealing their mob.<br>
4) SoT people run to our camp with a few mobs and KS Treah that we were fighting.<br>
<br>
Can I understanb their frustration at having a mob they had worked toward stolen? Yes.<br>
I can even understand (not condone) their FFA and KSing the mob without thinking of the consequences in the heat of the moment.<br>
<br>
I am willing to understand what SoT was thinking at the time. Again, I ask you SoT guys to give us the same chance and try to understand what we were doing and thinking at the time:<br>
<br>
1) RF goes to PoG and setup camp at waterfall and pulls Treah without killing the  protectors as RF always do (different tactics I guess) but unfortunately some extra<br>
  mobs show up and RF loose the fight.<br>
2) RF goes on a CR.<br>
3) RF goes back to waterfall with the intent of killing Treah again.<br>
4) RF pulls Treah without killing protectors not knowing SoT was thinking it was theirs.<br>
5) SoT calls FFA and run with some mobs to RF camp and KS Treah.<br>
<br>
Can SoT understand the frustration of having our camp trained during a fight and have a mob KSed from us? I certainly hope so. Maybe calling the GMs wasnt the best solution but just as the decision from SoT to KS us this was probably done in the heat of the moment too.<br>
<br>
One thing everybody on this thread seems to agree, this wouldnt have happened with better communication. SoT didnt know we were going for Treah just as RF didnt know<br>
SoT was going for Treah. Since RF doesnt kill protectors before pulling Treah, the fact that SoT was killing protectors (which RF probably didnt even notice) didnt give them a<br>
clue as to SoT intent.<br>
<br>
Only thing I can hope from this book I have written here is to have both our guilds come to better terms again. One thing I know for sure is RF intentions were never to use SoT work killing the protectors as an easy way to kill Treah. This is not RF way and if our SoT friends take the time to understand that, maybe we can put all this behind us.<br>
<br>
Balduk Swiftmind<br>
Forever 55th wizard<br>
Raging Fury<br>
